You can blend up to six datasets. Add all datasets before beginning to explore them. The query result shows the relationship between data for each dataset.

Data blending differs from a join operation in that it affects only the data visualization. With data blending, you can reveal relationships across multiple datasets without altering the datasets.

To extend your exploration further, add more datasets. You can query up to four datasets in a single exploration.

To create a meaningful side-by-side comparison, select measures and fields from each dataset. Define groups, measures, and filters by selecting fields from any of the blended datasets. 

Note: When blending data from multiple datasets, faceting applies only to the primary dataset, record-level actions work only with the primary dataset, and drill and focus features are not available.
